> I am not sure Iâ€™m following. If we get a request to reallocate for a different node then we should either reject it or do the new allocation for this new node and copy the data to the new place. Shrinking the allocation on the old node doesnâ€™t seem to be right. Or am I missing something?
> 
If your process migrates to a new NODE, which is fine, it does not mean
that you have to perform all this bouncing movement(reallocate on a new node).
Next time it can be migrated back. Process are allowed to migrate and access
to a remote memory.

Let's keep it simple.

